HEADWORD: Poacher
<hw>Poach"er</hw> <pr>(p⟦omac⟧ch"⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>One who poaches; one who kills or catches game or fish
contrary to law.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The American widgeon.</def>
<mark>[Local, U.S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Sea poacher</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>the
lyrie.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Poachiness</ent>⟦br⟧
